line_1: Stand now and judge thyself — hast thou incurr'd
line_2: His anger who can waste thee with a word,
A plague so little to be fear'd,

line_1: Some Lords your anger have incurr'd,
line_2: But if you'l take the Nations word,

line_1: Some Lords your anger have incurr'd,
line_2: Most People think it was absurd,

line_1: After so many Hardships and Dangers incurr'd,
line_2: He Himself thinks He ought to be better preferr'd;
